  "security_invariants": [
    "Wake payloads select registered runtime profiles; they never carry arbitrary shell commands.",
    "Host credentials are project scoped and limited to runner and IXP operations.",
    "Host secrets never enter Switchboard activity, snapshots, messages, or wake results.",
    "A message stored in a mailbox is not runtime delivery proof; acknowledgement is handling proof.",
    "A wake completes only after runtime registration or another explicit ready-state receipt.",
    "Work-capable hosts require allow_work=true and explicit allowed_lanes; lane-less wakes are inbox-only.",
    "Snapshot, kill, restart, and resume require a host-owned process, vendor session id, or checkpoint handle.",
    "resume_required never falls back to a fresh conversation; resume_preferred records a typed fallback before starting fresh.",
    "Missing registration, liveness, capacity, launcher, handle, or checkpoint denies the capability."
  ],
